						<h1>Richard Pollack</h1>
						<h5>Firefighter, Truck 44</h5>
						<span class=norm>
						<strong>Age:</strong> 37<br>
						<br>
						<strong>Years on the job:</strong> 13<br>
						<br>
						<strong>What made you decide to become a Fireman?</strong><br>
						Rich Pollack, a firefighter with the Chicago Fire Department says that being a fireman has always been a dream for him.  “Being a fireman has always been a family thing for 
						me.” Pollack’s grandfather, father and uncle were all firemen before him.  “That’s one of the things I love most about being a fireman, the sense of family that you get from 
						this job.”  “I also like the fact that we help out when people need us.”  When Pollack isn’t busy helping people or fighting fires he enjoys building motorcycles, boxing and 	
						collecting old vintage auto parts.<br>
						<br>
						<strong>What is your idea of a perfect night out in Chicago?</strong><br>
						A great meal, preferably sushi followed by some live music.  Chicago is a great town for live music especially jazz and blues.  Also, some good company never hurts for a great 						night out in Chicago!<br>
						<br>
						<strong>How would you like to be remembered?</strong><br>
						I would like to be remembered as honest, confident, caring, positive and helpful.<br>
						<br>
						<strong>Were you the teacher’s pet or the class clown?</strong> <br>
						Neither!  I was always the quiet shy kid who never had any girlfriends!<br>
						<br>
						<strong>If you could live anywhere other than Chicago where would that be?</strong><br>
						I would probably live on the west coast somewhere around Los Angeles.<br>
						<br>
						<strong>What’s the thing you love most about being a fireman?</strong><br>
						Not only does my job enable me to help others but it also gives me plenty of spare time to spend with someone special.
						<br>
